(Constraint
    "The canonical commit form is jj commit -m '<msg>'. Don't use jj describe @ -m '<msg>' on the working copy — describe is for already-committed parents only. skills/jj.md forbids describe-on-@ explicitly."
    "you shouldnt use describe, and you should push the working copy, so I dont know why youre documenting the use of @ - doesnt the skill forbid the use of describe?"
    "Correcting my repeated use of jj describe in routine work; landed in skills/jj.md as an explicit forbidden form."
    Maximum
    2026-05-18T17:05:03Z)

(Clarification
    "jj commit accepts paths as positional arguments — jj commit <my-paths> -m '<msg>' commits only the named files. The simple default for path-selective commits, alongside jj split which is used when bookmarks need to move forward."
    "you can pick the files to commit with jj commit I believe."
    "Pointing out that I had been documenting jj split as if it were the only path-selective option; jj commit is the simpler form for same-parent commits with no bookmark motion."
    Medium
    2026-05-18T17:06:23Z)
